# GCP Firewall Security Lab

## Secure Remote Access Implementation using Google Cloud VPC Firewall Rules

### Author

Nitin Sukthe

### Role

Future Cloud Security Engineer 

### Platform

Google Cloud Platform (GCP)

### Project Type

Cloud Network Security Lab

### Date

June 2026

---

# Executive Summary

This project demonstrates the implementation of secure network access controls within Google Cloud Platform (GCP) using VPC Firewall Rules and Compute Engine.

The primary objective was to reduce the attack surface of a cloud-hosted virtual machine by restricting SSH access (TCP Port 22) to a trusted source IP address rather than allowing unrestricted Internet access.

The project follows cloud security best practices including:

* Principle of Least Privilege
* Network Segmentation
* Source IP Restriction
* Secure Administrative Access
* Attack Surface Reduction

The environment was deployed, tested, validated, and securely decommissioned after completion.

---

# Project Objectives

The goals of this lab were:

### Infrastructure Security

* Deploy a secure Compute Engine VM
* Configure network-level access controls
* Validate administrative access

### Network Security

* Restrict SSH access using firewall policies
* Apply network tags to control traffic
* Limit inbound access to a trusted IP

### Cloud Security Operations

* Verify security configurations
* Validate firewall effectiveness
* Document cloud security controls

